=begin pod
=head2 start-editing

Begins editing on a C<$cell-editable>.

The L<Gnome::Gtk4::CellRenderer|/content-docs/api2/reference/Gtk4/CellRenderer> for the cell creates and returns a L<Gnome::Gtk4::R-CellEditable|/content-docs/api2/reference/Gtk4/R-CellEditable> from
gtk_cell_renderer_start_editing(), configured for the L<Gnome::Gtk4::CellRenderer|/content-docs/api2/reference/Gtk4/CellRenderer> type.

C<.start-editing()> can then set up C<$cell-editable> suitably for
editing a cell, e.g. making the Esc key emit L<Gnome::Gtk4::R-CellEditable|/content-docs/api2/reference/Gtk4/R-CellEditable>::editing-done`.

Note that the C<$cell-editable> is created on-demand for the current edit; its
lifetime is temporary and does not persist across other edits and/or cells.

=begin code
method start-editing ( N-Object() $event )
=end code

=item $event; The L<Gnome::Gdk4::Event|/content-docs/api2/reference/Gdk4/Event> that began the editing process, or
  undefined if editing was initiated programmatically.

