=begin pod
=head1 Signals

=comment -----------------------------------------------------------------------
=head3 editing-done

This signal is a sign for the cell renderer to update its
value from the C<$cell-editable>.

Implementations of L<Gnome::Gtk4::R-CellEditable|/content-docs/api2/reference/Gtk4/R-CellEditable> are responsible for
emitting this signal when they are done editing, e.g.
L<Gnome::Gtk4::Entry|/content-docs/api2/reference/Gtk4/Entry> emits this signal when the user presses Enter. Typical things to
do in a handler for I<editing-done> are to capture the edited value,
disconnect the C<$cell-editable> from signals on the L<Gnome::Gtk4::CellRenderer|/content-docs/api2/reference/Gtk4/CellRenderer>, etc.

C<.editing-done()> is a convenience method
for emitting L<Gnome::Gtk4::R-CellEditable|/content-docs/api2/reference/Gtk4/R-CellEditable>::editing-done`.

=begin code
method handler (
  Int :$_handle_id,
  N-GObject :$_native-object,
  Gnome::Gtk4::CellEditable :$_widget,
  *%user-options
)
=end code

=item $_handle_id; The registered event handler id.
=item $_native-object; The native object provided by the Raku object which registered this event. This is a native B<Gnome::Gtk4::CellEditable> object.
=item %user-options; A list of named arguments provided by L<.register-signal() in class Object|/content-docs/api2/reference/GObject/Object#register-signal>.

